"Abstract With the Web, there is a little more preventative work that can be done to prevent abuse than with email. URL filters, although I fundamentally oppose them from an engineering design point-of-view 1 , are a necessary and unpleasant evil in the corporate world. They can prevent the vast majority of the innocent and casual browsing of offensive and similar material, although the dedicated seeker after pornography will always be able to find sites that have not yet been picked up by the filter database team."
